1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:07,223
The first shift is simple: stop measuring AI work by the number of messages and start measuring the artifact or change produced.

2
00:00:07,173 --> 00:00:11,076
The research distinguishes consultation from delegated production.

3
00:00:11,076 --> 00:00:14,298
Consultation gives you information or suggestions.

4
00:00:14,298 --> 00:00:22,413
Delegated production asks the system to create a document, transform data, modify a system, validate a change, or complete a workflow.

5
00:00:22,413 --> 00:00:34,634
That difference appears across many tasks: drafting a memo from source files, cleaning a spreadsheet and checking totals, debugging a failing application, preparing a campaign, or producing structured research with citations.

6
00:00:34,634 --> 00:00:39,394
Task horizon is evidence that users trust agents with larger pieces of work.

7
00:00:39,394 --> 00:00:52,201
By May 2026, eighty point six percent of sampled individual users had made a request estimated above thirty minutes of human work, seventy point two percent above one hour, and twenty-five point six percent above eight hours.

8
00:00:52,201 --> 00:00:56,163
The broadest request also tends to arrive at the beginning of a thread.

9
00:00:56,163 --> 00:00:59,500
Later turns are narrower corrections and refinements.

10
00:00:59,500 --> 00:01:06,567
Good delegation therefore begins with a complete work packet, not with a vague sentence followed by twenty rounds of missing context.

11
00:01:06,567 --> 00:01:09,509
Intensive users organize work differently.

12
00:01:09,509 --> 00:01:15,846
They run longer tasks, reuse skills, and sometimes coordinate several independent agents in parallel.

13
00:01:15,846 --> 00:01:23,769
The human role shifts from typing every step to defining work, monitoring progress, reviewing evidence, and deciding where to intervene.

14
00:01:23,769 --> 00:01:25,711
Treat the numbers carefully.

15
00:01:25,711 --> 00:01:30,259
Human-time estimates are generated by a model and should be read as directional.

16
00:01:30,259 --> 00:01:40,961
OpenAI employees also work in an unusually favorable environment with broad access, low friction, and strong internal knowledge sharing, so their adoption pattern is not a promise for every team.

17
00:01:40,961 --> 00:01:42,500
Chapter recap.

18
00:01:42,500 --> 00:01:47,278
First, measure the artifact or change produced, not the number of messages.

19
00:01:47,278 --> 00:01:53,240
Second, delegate a complete work packet rather than revealing essential context one correction at a time.

20
00:01:53,240 --> 00:01:59,887
Third, treat task-horizon data as evidence of a shift, not as proof that every long task belongs to an agent.
